DAMATURU – Senator Ibrahim Mohammed Bomai, representing Yobe South Senatorial district, has donated two million naira to the Christian community in the four Local Government Areas Potiskum, Fune, Fika and Nangere, all in his senatorial zone for the celebration of Christmas. Receiving the donation on behalf of the four local government areas, an official of Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN), Mr. Thomas Yaroro, thanked the lawmaker for the kind gesture, saying, “this will go a long way in putting smiles on the faces of our people.” It would be recalled that last year, Senator Bomai extended same gesture for the Christmas celebration in his area. Musa Ibrahim Musale represented the Senator during the presentation.